---
// Drop-in Spacing foundation body. The scale is inherited unchanged by every
// spoke (re-skin color + type, not density), so the token names come straight
// from the manifest; each bar paints at its real token width and its value/px
// labels hydrate live.
import Section from './Section.astro';
import { spacingScale } from './tokens';
import { withBase } from './base';

interface Props { brand?: string; brandHref?: string }
const { brand, brandHref = '/design-system' } = Astro.props;
---
{brand && (
  <nav class="crumbs">
    <a href={withBase(brandHref)}>{brand}</a> <span>/</span> <span>Foundations</span> <span>/</span> <span>Spacing</span>
  </nav>
)}
<h1>Spacing</h1>
<p class="lede">
  A single linear-then-modular scale drives every gap, pad and margin. Inherited from the
  hub unchanged — use tokens, never raw pixels, so density stays consistent across the kit.
</p>

<Section id="scale" title="Spacing scale">
  <p>Each bar renders at its real token width. Steps climb in 2&ndash;4px increments through the dense UI range, then jump to layout-scale spacing.</p>
  <div class="scale">
    {spacingScale.map((token) => (
      <div class="row">
        <div class="row__meta">
          <code>--{token}</code>
          <span><span data-token-value={token}>—</span> · <span data-token-px={token}>—</span></span>
        </div>
        <div class="row__track"><div class="row__bar" style={`width: var(--${token})`}></div></div>
      </div>
    ))}
  </div>
</Section>

<Section id="usage" title="Usage">
  <p>Reach for the dense steps (<code>050</code>&ndash;<code>400</code>) inside controls and cards; the larger steps (<code>500</code>+) for section and page rhythm.</p>
  <pre class="snippet"><code>{`.card {
  padding: var(--spacing-400);   /* 16px */
  gap: var(--spacing-300);       /* 12px */
}
.section + .section {
  margin-top: var(--spacing-700); /* 48px */
}`}</code></pre>
</Section>

<script>import './foundation-hydrate';</script>

<style>
  .scale { display: flex; flex-direction: column; }
  .row { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 200px minmax(0, 1fr); align-items: center; gap: var(--spacing-400); padding: var(--spacing-250) 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border-light); }
  .row:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .row__meta { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 2px; }
  .row__meta code { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--color-text-primary); }
  .row__meta span { font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--color-text-muted); }
  .row__track { min-width: 0; overflow-x: auto; }
  .row__bar { height: 22px; border-radius: 5px; background: var(--color-primary); min-width: 2px; }

  .snippet { background: var(--color-surface-sunken); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 10px; padding: var(--spacing-400) var(--spacing-500); overflow-x: auto; }
  .snippet code { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 13.5px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--color-text-primary); background: none; padding: 0; }
</style>
